#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn36.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga "
msgstr "1. With Verses "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Phassamūlakasutta "
msgstr "10. Rooted in Contact "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.215, sc1
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.1"
msgid "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, vedanā phassajā phassamūlakā phassanidānā phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these three feelings are born, rooted, sourced, and conditioned by contact. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso? "
msgstr "What three? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.3"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.4"
msgid "Sukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "Pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.5"
msgid "Tasseva sukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā, yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā sukhā vedanā, sā nirujjhati, sā vūpasammati. "
msgstr "With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as pleasant, the corresponding pleasant feeling ceases and stops. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.6"
msgid "Dukkhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr "Painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.7"
msgid "Tasseva dukkhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā, yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ dukkhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā dukkhā vedanā, sā nirujjhati, sā vūpasammati. "
msgstr "With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as painful, the corresponding painful feeling ceases and stops. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.8"
msgid "Adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā. "
msgstr "Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.9"
msgid "Tasseva adukkhamasukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā, yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā adukkhamasukhā vedanā, sā nirujjhati, sā vūpasammati. "
msgstr "With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as neutral, the corresponding neutral feeling ceases and stops. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā → saṅkhattā tassa samodānā (s1, s2, km) | saṅghaṭṭā tassa samodhānā (s3) | saṅghattā tassa samodhānā (mr)
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ kaṭṭhānaṃ saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā usmā jāyati, tejo abhinibbattati. Tesaṃyeva kaṭṭhānaṃ nānābhāvā vinikkhepā, yā tajjā usmā, sā nirujjhati, sā vūpasammati. "
msgstr "When you rub two sticks together, heat is generated and fire is produced. But when you part the sticks and lay them aside, any corresponding heat ceases and stops. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.11"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, imā tisso vedanā phassajā phassamūlakā phassanidānā phassapaccayā. "
msgstr "In the same way, these three feelings are born, rooted, sourced, and conditioned by contact. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.12"
msgid "Tajjaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca tajjā vedanā uppajjanti. "
msgstr "The appropriate feeling arises dependent on the corresponding contact. "

msgctxt "sn36.10:1.13"
msgid "Tajjassa phassassa nirodhā tajjā vedanā nirujjhantī”ti. "
msgstr "When the corresponding contact ceases, the appropriate feeling ceases.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.14"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.10:1.15"
msgid "Vedanāsaṃyuttassa sagāthāvaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.1"
msgid "Samādhi sukhaṃ pahānena, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.2"
msgid "pātālaṃ daṭṭhabbena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.3"
msgid "Sallena ceva gelaññā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.10:2.4"
msgid "anicca phassamūlakāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
